clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For the treatment of symptoms of dry mouth in patients with Sj ouml gren s Syndrome

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Cevimeline is a cholinergic agonist which binds to muscarinic receptors Muscarinic agonists in sufficient dosage can increase secretion of exocrine glands such as salivary and sweat glands and increase tone of the smooth muscle in the gastrointestinal and urinary tracts
